description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for three Band 5 Occupational Therapist&#39;s to join the Home Safe Team on a fixed term basis (2 x 6 month posts and 1 x 12 month post). They will be based across various Sites. The successful applicants need to be flexible in their approach and be willing to work across sites as and when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is an integrated multi-disciplinary team that proactively facilitates a safe, effective and timely patient discharge and aims to prevent re-admission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team will have a holistic focus on the entire patient journey where discharge planning begins at the point of admission to NSECH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant must have excellent communication skills be able to work on their own initiative and as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have a diploma/degree in occupational therapy and be able to demonstrate on-going professional development. Applicants must be able to meet the transport requirements of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will have access to regular management and reflective supervision, annual appraisals and professional development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Essential Criteria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diploma or degree in Occupational Therapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State registered with Health and Care Professions Council&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 16/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
